consistent gap between them.\"", "\"WEIGHTED AVERAGE CONTRIBUTION TO SALES RATIO\":The \"WEIGHTED AVERAGE CONTRIBUTION TO SALES RATIO\" is a financial metric used to assess the impact of altering the mix of products produced and sold on the overall profitability. It is calculated by dividing the total contribution by the total revenue, expressed as the weighted average contribution to sales ratio (WA C/S ratio). This ratio helps in understanding how changes in product mix can affect the overall financial performance of a business.", "\"BREAK-EVEN SALES REVENUE\":\"This quiz involves calculating the break-even sales revenue for a company producing multiple products, given the product mix ratio, contribution to sales ratio for each product, and general fixed costs.\"", "\"MARGIN OF SAFETY IN UNITS\":\"This quiz involves calculating the margin of safety in units for a company that makes a single product, given the selling price per unit, fixed costs, contribution/sales ratio, and sales revenue.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}